subSubSection.paragraph:
The earliest European record of
P.meini
is reported from Spain , thereby suggesting that this species entered Europe from North-Western Africa at the end of the Turolian ( Agustí & Llenas 1996 ;
van Dam et al. 2001
;
Agustí et al. 2006a
). At the beginning of the Ruscinian, its geographical range broadened to the Eastern sector of the Mediterranean, as testified by the Maritsa record (
de Bruijn et al. 1970
).
